\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could I have your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Lilah Olive Hudson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 43 Thompson Street East, Horrowgate Hill, Darlington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And you're husband's still alive isn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could you tell me the year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 1935.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And the year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Sheffield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many years did you live in the house at Sheffield where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh just over a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did you move to from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Came straight back to Darlington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember the address in Sheffield or any details about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't know but on the birth certificate it simply says Brightsides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you came to Darlington where did you live in Darlington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The first place I think I came to was Gurney Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How long were you in Gurney Street before you moved?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - about four or five years I think. Then we moved to Shildon Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How long were you in Shildon Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I was about - twenty - twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It'd be after 1918 wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes, about twenty-one. Then we moved to Katherine Street. Oh yes, it was the - the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So Shildon Street would be the house in which you lived the longest as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember why the family made these moves, why did they move to Darlington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well my dad was a moulder. And I think he worked before I was born at Manchester first, he moved to Manchester. Then he moved from Manchester to Sheffield. Then I don't know what happened but he decided he'd come back to Darlington to the Darlington
 Forge. That's where he came back to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Why did they move from Gurney Street to Shildon Street, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I had - four brothers and no sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many brothers were older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 One brother was eight years older than me. And - then three brothers were younger than I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How much younger were they, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well there was five years between four of us, so you can reckon up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The four of you were born within five years you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 near}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 to you was the next brother to you, would he just be a year younger then or two years?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Just a year and a little bit I think between each one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I - I think he'd be - thirty-one. I think - I - I - just grasping it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old was he when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Seventy-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 1950.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did your father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  Weardale.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And was he always a moulder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, he served his time at the steelworks in Wolsingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he have another job at all before he became a moulder or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. His mother wanted him to be a draughtsman, he was very clever. But he went one day and saw the moulders wor
king at the work. He said, I want to be a moulder. He got wrong for it like but - he still did what he wanted to do. But - he was - he - she wanted him to be a professional violinist as well. He was very good at the violin. But - very obstinate, so he stu
ck to what he - that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was he a moulder when he died or did he do something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 He stayed a moulder }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  to retire during the war years through ill health. He was only in his fifties - when - he hadn't worked for over that twenty odd years - in the trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So what did he do then when he had to retire through ill health?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well we got a milk - we - had a milk business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 This is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 during}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  the first world war is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. My eldest brother had to go 
to the war, he was eight years older than me I've told you, he was eighteen when he went so I was twelve and - mother got this milk business. As children used to take it out before we went to school. Mother used to take it and father stayed in the house, 
s
erved the customers that came and washed up and whatnot and we - we managed. And we had it 'til the second world war Yes, and the two - two brothers younger than me had the business. Then the second world war come and they took them. Both, first the older
 one was a year older and they took him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father also do any casual or part time jobs, you said he was a violinist, what did he do about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh, just used to play at - dances and - silver weddings and such things as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 This is before 1918 is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Just when he was - through ill health when he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Before you got the milk business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. I think it was the dust - in the factory got on his chest - and got bronchitis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But he'd still carry on playing the violin during that time would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. He was all right after he came out the factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So the milk business was your father's last job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well in those days - in those days there wasn't any dole was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So the milk business was the only job he had after was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. But he didn't - go out with any milk. Stayed in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 An played the violin?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well she was two years older than dad so she would be thirty-three.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The same place as dad. Wolsingham. She was a farmer's daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she help on the farm before she was married or have a different job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She just helped at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she work at all after she was married or not, you said she helped with this business up to the end of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She never worked 'til she was married 'til we got this milk business. The f
irst world war, the beginning of the first world war, 1915 it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And she carried on with this until he passed it over to your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, it was still her business. Right up to the second world war. But the two brothers worked in it because 
they got - extended the business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And then she sold it to the Northern Dairies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Dairies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother have any other part time jobs at all or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When your mother was working in the milk business who looked after the children or did you all work in together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
We all worked in together. We used to - me youngest brother was seven, he used to take so many cans of milk round, second one. Of course, we all did that before nine o'clock in the morning. And then - I w
as twelve and of course that's all we had to do 'til - we finished schooling. Then when I was finished schooling of course I took it out. But mother was the one that took it round the streets in two cans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Of course your father would be at home to help with the children wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Yes. Well we were at school part time weren't we during the war. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many rooms were there in the house at Shildon Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Four. Four - four like and they used call it in those days sculleries didn't they Four rooms. So -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many bedrooms would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Two bedrooms and - front room, they used to call them front rooms in those days, living room and kitchenette. They call it kitchens - sculleries they used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers live in the house, did you have any relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It wasn't sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Your mother did it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. And I used to help. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother mend or make the family's clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mother mended everything and darned - everything was beautifully darned in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She was a very good needlewoman was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were your clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I think they were new when we first got them. Just depends. I know afterwards, I can remember taking all our small things down to a person that
 had a large family, you know, a bit lower down the street. Passing them on. I should - I should imagine we would probably get some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  other people, I don't know how they did in those days. Can't remember quite as far back as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father mend or make any of the family's clothes, did he mend shoes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Yes. Oh yes, father cobbled all the shoes. And he cut the hairs. Yes, the boys' hairs. Yes. Then afterwards when I got up I got the job and I cut the boy's hairs, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 mother\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  hairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember where the clothes were bought, where did you used to have your new clothes from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well mother was a member of the Co-operative Society. They used to try to save a little bit of money on the dividend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When did you have new clothes, any particular time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well they used to get things for Easter. And by the way my father's mother was a - was a dressmaker and she used to always send me a new dress for every Easter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were your shoes always new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, always new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And your father mended them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where were your new shoes bought from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When did you have new shoes, any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, just at - just when we needed them. We never went with holes in our shoes. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Your father was a good cobbler was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he help with the cleaning at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well - he didn't - do the cleaning much but he did all the 
washing up, prepared vegetables for the dinner. Then when mother used to come in you see she'd get the dinner ready. Mother did all her own bread. Yes, he did everything like that. Was always doing - handyman about the house. Didn't actually clean. Well, 
he used to do the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 fireplaces}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he do any decorating at all, who did the decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, he never decorated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well - he used to have a friend used to come to paper for him. Mother used to do the whitewashing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I should say - he always did the dairy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he do any repairs or improvements to the house, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well it wasn't our own house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So that wasn't necessary then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember if helped to dress you or undress you, did he help in that way when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I supposed he did, I can't remember as far as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you ever remember him bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, but I remember we used to have - it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  Friday night and in tho
se days we used to have what they called a sofa with two arms on the end. And - we used to be waiting one another to get the bath, the bath would be in front of the fire. Was no bathrooms in those days. Friday night was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But you don't remember your father bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No, I can't go quite as far back. I don't think he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 He used to play to us. And we used to sit round, have a little concert. Lovely.
 Used to be - when we were children we always used to say, play the cuckoo dad. Just - used to play just like the cuckoo and - the Irish Washerwoman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you dance to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, I used to dance. He used to - oh he was very clever. It was him that
 taught me - timing. And when - after I first learned to - do the piano, about ten year old I would be, after that he used to come in and practice. Get me to go through and we used to do duets. Of course used to get wrong notes and he used to get wrong bu
t
 eventually we got the timing good. Through that - through him, I know he was strict but it was through hi that really - and when you are young that's the most important thing in music, timing. It always - you can always get notes correct after if you str
ike wrong notes, but it you never get your timing right from the beginning - it's chaos. \{ILLEGIBLE\} isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You had a good basic training from your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I can't remember that you kn
ow. Can't remember - I can't remember my childhood. No. I can remember from about ten year old, that's about all I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember if he eve took you out when you were ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. I'll tell you what - yes. Yes. We - father used to
 take me to the operatic - opera. Yes, the Carnival - the Doyle Carte Opera Company was at the old Hippodrome in those days. It wasn't the Civic, it was called the Hippodrome. And I can remember - I can remember going because we used to go in the - top of
 it - the gods as they called them. I can always remember going there and saw the Barber of Seville.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Ten. Just before I started music - started music when I was ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Anyone else used to go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 At - afterward - I used to go with him - turn his - music over when he used to go to parties. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 As soon as you could read music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It didn't matter if I didn't. He used to say, over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Father never went out very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I used to do the housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 All of it, while your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mother and I. No, we used to go out t
ogether. Then we came in and father would have a cup of tea in the morning - when we were finished you see, we had to walk, didn't ride in those days. Had to walk, and then - when we finished it would be about twelve o'clockish, or - just about twelve o'c
l
ock. Then we'd come home and have another cup of tea then we would have to start - father get the vegetables ready. Probably sometimes we'd have the dinner going and then the brothers used to come in from school and of course he looked after those if we h
adn't quite finished. Then we - had our lunch then we had all the washing up to do. And then we started - went with the milk at the night you know. Twice a day we used to do it in those days. So - you can tell there was quite a lot of work. Isn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And when you were at school you went to school in between times did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. And during the war - during the war we just did half - half time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The first world war, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You did half time at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 For - for about one or two years. That's all we could do. Not through our own fault.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So you had plenty of time to help with the milk business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But I - I passed - I passed the scholarship. I passed to go to the - Commercial School. But - in those days - I
 didn't pass for the High School eventually. I passed }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 the other one and the - the books were to pay - father couldn't afford them so - I just stayed on at school and I was put up - straight up into Ex-Seven. I was in there, and I was - I was monitor. Head girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have any other tasks apart from helping with the housework and milk round?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I just - the usual routine of home life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you carry on helping with the housework after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You always helped your mother did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your brothers have any particular }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 tasks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  they had to carry out regularly at all to help your mother and father, they helped with the milk round did they as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. They helped. And did odd jobs about the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of odd jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 My youngest brother was as good as a woman. Could do anything, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In the domestic line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. But the other brothers - one brother when he left school went to a farm. And the other one - went - to some work
s, forget which works it was now. Of course me oldest brother was away during the war. He was away five years. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 Don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 remember but - didn't come back 'til 1919 so he was out of it wasn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your older brother ever help the younger ones with things
 they found difficult, such as dressing or eating, or look after you in other ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I suppose he would do. Can't remember as far back as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever do anything for your younger brothers in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I know we had lots of fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 They didn't do any particular jobs for you to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 expected to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3411776\charrsid6187387 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh really I can't - remember, but
 I should imagine we would have to go pretty early being as we had to get up to deliver the milk the next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 About what time do you think it would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh about half seven I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Usually. I think mother used to put the younger ones to bed. We wouldn't be so very - I can only sort of remember from when we got the milk business so - I can't remember before that, so therefore - I should think we would be able to put ourselves to bed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What age do you think you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh about - seven - six or seven I should imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well mother eventually slept with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would you be then when you slept with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh - we had a camp bed first. I was in a little camp bed. Then when my brothers got a bit older - I think about - ten or eleven, mother - mother slept with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did your father sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Me father slept with me older brother. 
And then we had two - they had different beds you see. And then the other boys were in - and me other brother was in a single, he got my little single.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So you shared with your brothers until you were old enough to move out sort of thing and then you moved in with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I don't know, I should think when we were young we had a bath every night I should imagine. But when we got a bit older we - we always had a - well I think we had one ev
ery night because we hadn't time on the morning. So - I know we all had a good wash, very good wash. But on a Friday night we used to have a - our hairs; washed. Only had our hairs washed once a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Friday night was cleaning night was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh I should think - I think I had clean underclothes on practically every day. Mother was always washing. When we were little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Yes. Used to be - we used to eat in the front room, had a - put a table in there we used to eat in there. - Every time we had birthdays or a party or at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You went in the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did your mother do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well we had a scullery, and she used to prepare it on the kitchen table and - and we had a - the gas - a gas oven in the scullery but we had a coal oven in the living room. And she used to bak
e her bread. Oh well, mother used to always make the bread, brown bread and white bread. Two baking days a week she always had. She was a hard working woman was my mother. Incidentally I can't bear bread. No. But me mother could never make pastry very - v
e
ry successfully. She had too heavy a hand with doing the loaves of bread, you know. Yes. Afterwards, she always did make pastry, pies, but after I got going I got the job of doing all the pastry. Father used - made a contraption that went on the old fende
r, wood - to put all the loaf tins to rise before they went in the oven to bake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When was breakfast eaten, did you have it before you went on the milk round or after you got back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh before we went on the milk round because - we used to dash - wh
en we came back we had to dash straight back - straight to school. For nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So about what time would you have your breakfast, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 About half seven I think. Seven to half past.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were all the members of the family present for breakfast, did you all have breakfast together, was your father up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Father was always up first. And - well, father and mother, I don't know who got up first. But he used to shout at me, and he used to always have to come up to the bedroom door 
and knock on the bedroom door. I was always last - last up, me. Always have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember what you usually had to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well I - I - I'm sure we always had egg and bacon. We all loved it. And dip - I loved that. Dip your bread in - fried bread. Oh was that 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 delicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 , delicious that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What would you drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have anything different for breakfast on certain days, such as Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh might have probably sausage with - a
nd probably liver, I don't know. I know - you're asking about the breakfasts aren't you. Not about other meals. Breakfast yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have your main meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were all the members of the family present apart from the brother what was in the forces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you have then, what sort of a meal did you usually have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh we had - proper dinners, you know what I mean, not makeshift dinners, mother used to get - meat and - and she used to make l
ovely Yorkshire puddings, puddings. Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 gorgeous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 Yorkshire puddings. It was a treat to have the Yorkshire puddings. Had them twice a week. We always used to have them Sunday and the middle of the week. Of course when it got cold weather she used to make wha
t you call broth. Everything went into it. All the vegetables you could think of, the root vegetables and - split peas, barley, lentils - all - all the things that go in to make a good soup. And then she eventually did dumplings in it. And - after you'd h
ad a good dish of broth - you didn't want anything else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Incidentally I didn't like the dumplings. It's one thing I never - never did like. I still don't to this day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have anything different for lunch on certain days, what was Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well - she always used to get rump - is it rump - rump, yes, or sirloin. Always got - good meat. Oh me father used to do all the vegetables, you know, when we were out with the round and - we used to usually cook the - do it 
slowly and do it on a Saturday in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 Dutch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 oven and he used to do leeks inside it and parsnips. Have you ever had it, on the meat. Oh absolutely delicious, absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you still do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Because I don't get a - a joint - there's only two of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Anything else you remember that you had for your main dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have a drink at dinner time as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, we always - always finished with tea, we always had a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you do at teatime did you have a high tea or just a light afternoon tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, usually have high tea or something - well, used to have boiled eggs or - anything like that. I don't think in those days, I can't remember - I don't think they would have Heinz beans, I don't think they 
were thought of. But we used to use - when it got colder weather - awful lot of toast. The boys used to - used to take it in turns to sit round the fire to toast the bread. One would toast it then mother would butter it, get it quick enough you know. Pile
s of toast and then jam and marmalade. Home made jam by the way we used to have. Yes, we used to make our own jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have anything else before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. We always had - two of them liked cocoa - father liked cocoa. Cup of cocoa.
 I never liked cocoa. I didn't have cocoa. Oh yes, a glass of milk. Loads of milk we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother and father have their tea with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. We all - we've always had our meals together. Nobody ever sat back. Not mother and father first an
d then the children. Just like some families are now. We all sit together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Your mother or father baked their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And she made her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of jam did she make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh well, we had a garden you see an
d we had raspberries. And then she sometimes used to buy the strawberries when they - the people used to come round selling strawberries in baskets. Strawberries and - I think she made rhubarb jam as well. And - yes, and crabapple jelly. Oh and by the way
 we used to make our own curds; with the milk that we had left. So you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How do you make that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well you put it - you buy a proper rennet thing and you - you make the milk sour, then you - we had a great big colander and she put it through the col
ander, put the milk through. Eventually it goes - you've seen what they're like, curds, can't you. Yes. And then the whey, it used to come through in the bottom of a pail used to have a pail underneath. Stand this colander thing in it - over the top of th
e pail and then the whey would was at the bottom. And - oh that was a - that was a treat on baking day. We used to have the pies and - lovely. Curd pies with currants and raisins. Haven't you hard of them? What was it they call them in the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Rather like a Welsh cheesecake you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh well - they sell in the bakers. Oh yes. You buy - you can buy curds you know now. Yes. And you mix it - the curds, you beat your curds up in a - you buy your curds ordinary. That's all you have. Look awful to lo
ok at. You put them in a basin and sprinkle currants and sugar, spoonful or two of sugar, and an egg in, makes it beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother bottle any fruit or vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I'm sorry - yes, we didn't make pickles but we bought - we did our own - oh that was a job I didn't like - we used to do our own pickled onions. Little - you had to - you cried to death. And - I'm sorry, yes, pickled beetroot. But she didn't mak
e pickles as a - like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 piccalilli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 not like that. But we did pickled - yes, pickled onions and beetroot, the red beetroot, pickled beetroot we call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she make any wine for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Father did. Elderberry wine. Oh once had a - catastrophe 
and once in the back bedroom, he used to put it up there. And it all blew off one night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You couldn't see the ceiling for all the corks had flown out - oh, what a terrible mess it was. So father hadn't to put them upstairs an
ymore. Had a shelf in the corner of the bedroom. We didn't know where to put things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So you liked his wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, lovely wine, it was very good wine, Elderberry wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother or father make any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh I should think me father would. Was always doing things. You know, when you had colds, butter and sugar, you know, and the - when you had coughs and whatnot. He's a terrible fellow if you had a sore throat. You had to go - he used to make a funnel 
out of a piece of paper - and put this sulphur in. Get you to open your mouth, here - and blow this sulphur down this funnel, remember that. Oh yes, good for your sore throat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did he do with the sugar and butter, was that for coughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 Spoonful of that when you had a very, very, very bad cough. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Some butter and mix a bit of sugar with it, this - I never liked that, because I don't like butter really. - But - it stopped you from coughing, you know, when you're a terrible cough and you cough
 - a tickly cough and - children cough incessant. One of my brothers, by the way, had bronchitis. He had it from being three, I forgot about that. From being about three and when he got to - eleven was it, he was very ill indeed. They sat up night and day
 with him and I do remember that. And he had to be in one temperature. And - it was a just a - either way it went you see, but - he got rid of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. I don't know. Father made - father made - he was always making things. So probably he would do, I couldn't say. Probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father and mother grow their own vegetables and fruit, you had a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother help with the garden at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No, she hadn't time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And you had fruit trees as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And the boys helped when they got up a bit, in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. I never went in the garden, I only went to pick all the stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they ever buy any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You had most of it in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Well we had apple trees and raspberry bushes, blackcurrants. And if we didn't have them neighbours gave us them, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever have any tinned vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Any dried vegetables or dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Not dried vegetables, the only thing I think we did buy in dried was the peas. Steep peas, oh we used to love steep peas. I think they're sill lovely don't you. You soak overnight, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents keep any livestock for the family, any hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. Hens and eventually later on - when the boys got older, father started to keep pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would you be then would that be before the end of the first world war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It was just about then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Father. 'Cos we were older you see, he didn't have a lot to do in the house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you help him at all with the hens or the pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, me brothers did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember how many times a week you had meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh most days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 We used to get rabbits but we didn't poach them but they were a present from the far
mer where we got the - always got a goose for Christmas for our Christmas box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 From the farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family - could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so. Be - before - I don't
 know what happened before we had the business. I couldn't say, I can sort of only remember - from there, but after we made - well we had more money to spare on the things, but before that we didn't have much I don't suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How long would your father be off work before they got the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh about six month I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So that six months might have been a bit sticky mightn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Oh yes, mother - mother didn't have very much money at all then. All her savings had gone I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father have more to eat than the rest of you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I suppose so, couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You never noticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, you had to eat it 'cos if you didn't eat it me father would say, you'd eat it if you were on a hilltop. Used to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What was your parents' attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate, what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well father would always say, too porky to live. That - that's the saying he used to say, if you were on a hilltop you would eat it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have to stay there until you did eat it or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 compelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  to eat anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh no, you just asked - say, please pass the salt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, we were told to sit up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And did you have to hold your knife and fork in a certain way or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
But incidentally one of my brothers was left handed so he held his in the other - opposite hand. Yes. A fork in that hand - his knife in that hand, his fork in this. He used to eat. We always used to try but never could do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And you always had to sit up straight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, we never read at the table. But my - my husband's family all did. When they finished the meal, sat with the last cup of tea but we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 As soon as you were finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You didn't have to wait for everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And all the family sat at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How was the meal served, who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mother - mother always served.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was there any particular order in which you were served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well - sometimes probably - they weren't - maybe the boys were - weren't quite there so whoever was there
 would be served, and then this would follow on wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did the younger brothers sit before they could feed themselves, did you remember where they sat when they were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, we had a - a chair. The youngest brother had a hig
h chair, I've got a photograph of him somewhere - sitting in his high chair. It wasn't very high, it used to be on the floor and it had a tray in the front.'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where would that be near the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It would be near - yes, near the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mother would feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they have it at the same time as you had your meal, they were more or less round the table with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think they would - not the babies. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So when do you think they were able to join in the family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I think from about - five - five years old wouldn't it be. Four or - no, about four. The youngest one would be four. I'd be nine wouldn't I.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. We were just like sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she show affection for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well she showed affection to every one of us I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, you never used go tell him anything really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Your mother used to tell him everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, not any - not little personal things. You cold talk to him, oh yes, you could talk to him. But if we had any - little thing, used to tell mother. Mother was easy going
, father - used to get bad tempered. Little bad tempered. He was a bit irritable. I'm a bit like him at times, yes. You know, we want things done, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh he must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 If you had and big worries could you share them with your father or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't think I did have any worries, not really worries, when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How do you mean? What do you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You said you treated your mother like a sister didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have to show respect to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Yes. Always called him father. Father and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they expect you to behave in any certain way towards them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think they ever did anything really wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How do you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they ever tell you what you must do or must not do as far as your brothers were concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they say if you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I don't think they said to me but they did to my brothers. They used to come in and say so and so had hit him. If a boy had hit - hit one of them, he used to say, well fight him back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - I don't think - I don't think they were so ambitious, you know, that they thought - enter universities or anything like 
that. They wanted us to be - to be able to look after ourselves and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Such as what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was there anything particular they said about things that were right or wrong, what things did they consider wrong?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well - at that time there used to be, just as there is now, crime - a lot of crime, you know, pilfering and whatnot. And they used to tell us, never take anything that doesn't belong to you. That was instilled int
o us. If we ever went into a room, we saw anything, we weren't tempted to pick it up. It's the same nowadays, I have stuff laid on - children coming here, and they never - I think it's really how you're brought up. Don't you? It's instilled into you. That
 you never think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 To be honest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Anything else that they considered right or wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't know. Loads of things but I just can't - I can't think of them at present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh they didn't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I think more or less, as long as we didn't - we used to sit and listen, more or less, if they were all in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could you join in if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well, father was very strict. Mother would - mother would say, if you don't do what you're told, you know what your dad'll do to you. So that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How did your father punish you? Were you ever smacked or sent to bed or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Told you couldn't go out, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you ever smacked at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I can't remember. He was always going to, but we always run away. We missed it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But you were stopped from going out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Yes, if we didn't do what we were told to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And were your brothers punished often or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well I can't - I don't think they ever did anything really wro
ng or - or that. They were - they were boys, they used to - I'll tell you what they used to get wrong for. They used to go climbing in those days, they'd come home and one of them would have a tear in his pants or something like that. And he'd get a good 
reprimanding you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother ever have to punish you at all or did she always pass it on to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, she just have to say - she'd just have to threaten us, I'll tell your father. And that was enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No. I can remember - that house we lived in - one of the brothers - there was some what you call Black - no, what do they call them, Blacklocks is it. And they were at the side of the fireplace, they'd come fro
m next door, I always remember that. And there was one or two but dad got rid of them with fumigating the cupboard thing beside the fireplace. But this particular time, one of us had got a blacklock. And they put it in a matchbox. They chased me all over 
the house. Screaming. Up and down - eeh - nearly went hysterical. And I've been scared of those ever since. Oh yes. Can't bear to see one in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was he punished for doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I think so. No, I just - just lad's tricks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well - naturally I resented it, but looking back over years I think it's really the best thing that can happen to anyone because it shows that it's disciplines isn't it, in some way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And you think disciplines a good thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I do. I think far too many children nowadays are spoiled because their mothers just give in. Mothers and fathers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a mor
e important part than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I think from both parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
When you had a birthday would it be different form any other day, you told me you usually had your birthday party in the front room didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Yes. Boys used to buy a little article each and - and I used to always could - I could invite a friend. As the years got on you see you could have more. Boys and girls at the party. I think the last one I had was fourteen - when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many did you have to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh about ten or twelve. Then or twelve. Six boys, six girls I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have anything special go eat at these parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, we always had a birthday cake. And jellies. Mother used to make
 - blancmanges. Always had loads of milk with having a milk party - with having the milk. And - and I think there was a friend of ours used to ice the cakes. Of course I forgot to tell you. We - afterwards, I said yesterday that we always went to the Co-o
p
. But after we got the milk business, that was before that, after we got the milk business we used to deal with the traders who bought the milk from us you see. We still went to the Co-op, we didn't have any clothiers, shoes or - or clothes or anything li
k
e that but - our groceries, mother went to - what you call a family grocer isn't it, in those days, there were loads of those. We had quite a lot of shopkeepers. So we - sort of ration going to different places and had a bran cake shop on the North Road c
alled the Miss Wards. So I definitely know we used to get their cakes, were delicious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you do with your guests on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh, we well we played games. At that time up to - this Postman's Knock. All those kind of sloppy games. And 
then we - probably I would entertain on the piano, 'cos I was - oh I started when I was ten, I was always very quick, learnt pretty quick. And - it got a bit rough I think, that was the last party I had when I got fourteen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 Rough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  boys. That finished - it finished it. 'Cos our boys weren't in then. They were just my own special guests then. That time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Not really. We just all were a - happy family. Used to 
buy one another things. And of course - in the winter months, forgot to tell you this, the milk business, we just used to deliver once a day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When the weather was bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well, yes, the - when it come to the daylight savings bill, the - the milk u
sed to come in just once a day and you used to have what you call the previous night's milk and you have two cans then when you took them out. One with the morning milk and one with last night's. So talk about - keeping up with customers you see. Which is
 fresh milk, which is the other? I mean, there was nothing wrong with it, just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 that one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 was last night's and one was this morning's. Nowadays you don't know, you have it all three days old don't you. Oh yes, yes. So when I used to go to one lady, very parti
cular, two basins, always used to put your jugs because it was laded - ladled out of the can you see, nothing bottled in those days. And - she always had a special one for the morning milk and the one for the other. Daren't put it in any other. One had a 
l
ip on, one basin had a lip. That had to be the morning milk. And the little round basin - you wouldn't think people would be so choosy would you. So therefore we had more time at home in the winter you see, we didn't have to go out. For about three or fou
r month. Start about the - spring weather again I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go to church at all on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Yes. Yes. Used to go to - I was confirmed. By the Bishop of Durham. I used to go to St Paul's church. I was in the choir. So I had to attend there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 you sing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  in the choir on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did all the family go and hear you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No. I was the only one that went to the church. My brothers went to the Wesleyan. Then after the boys - me mother used to attend didn't bother go so they wouldn't go. The brother next to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 me}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 went, he was the last one, he - he stayed the longest. But - me father said, well, if he didn't want to go - they had other - they had a lot of hobbies. Of course we had - I forgot to tell you - we had a dog
 as well, we had a dog and he used to go walks, country lads they were you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Is there anything else that you remember that you did with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't think so, not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What musical instruments did you have in the home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well we had the piano. Violin. Well we had numerous violins. And - the one - the brother that was - younger than me, played an }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 . Now he was always very good but he didn't learn off from music. Just learnt by ear, b
ut he was very good. And he could also play the mouth organ very good. That was the only one that ever had - any inclination towards music. The others could sing. Sing, pretty good singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But just one brother played the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  and mouth organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And he was self taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did anyone else play the piano as well as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother play anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. It's rather funny that, on mother's side I don't think there's anybody - who know there's about ten in the family, an
d there wasn't a one played anything. Me father's side was the artistic side. His sister used to - was - brought up in those days in a convent. We - we weren't Catholics you know but - she was taught by the sisters. Paintings all over the place, beautiful
 paintings. She win - she used to win at all the - you know, the shows liked what we have now, the W.I. shows and - and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 townswoman\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  guilds shows. Very good she was. So the talent - the talent was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You told me your brothers sang, did anyone else sing, you sing yourself don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. I went to singing lessons - in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did all your brothers sing, did your father sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, he was a wobbly singer though but he - he was there. But he - he didn't make it a - soloist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who would you say the singers in the family were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh me oldest brother liked to sing a bit but - there weren't - there weren't anybody trained but me. I was the only one that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When did you start having your singing lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The same person that I went to the piano lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you start at the same time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, I started about - twelve I think. I just had - we started with piano before me father was out of work. And then afterwards - I sort of left and this teacher left and 
had to transfer to another person. Then we got the business. And I was really keen to start again so I went to another person, I was about sixteen then. And after that I - that's when I went in for my exam. I said, well, if I couldn't teach, I wanted to b
e a teacher, if I couldn't teach I were going to teach the piano. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You told me you made music together as a family, could you describe a sort of musical evening you had all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. All the old things, Christmas Day we'd have the car
ols and father would play the carols and - sit - get round the piano, you know what I mean, like that. Those that didn't know the words would come and look }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  your shoulder and have a go at it. And - then we used to play - father's favourite was waltz - 
were waltz's Blue Danube, you know, and Strauss waltzes, yes, and things like that. As we got higher, as we got older. Higher in the culture of music. But - I think for - for the family while we were at home there were more popular things, I told you yest
erday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father play the violin and you play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And the others sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes, he had it on - on himself. No, well he could accompany, he could join in. Yes. Or sometimes he got his mouth organ out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did your mother do while you were all doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh doing the washing up or something in the back probably. Then she'd come in. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Any other occasion you remember particularly when you made music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh yes, sometimes - my father - had some friends that always liked him to play and he would - invite them round some evening, their wives and that and - we had quite a few Sunday evenings like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You played the piano for them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, loads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Ludo, snakes and ladders, draughts and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your brothers join in too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Family games were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Used to fight with those. But we never played cards. And we never played for money. Played for matchsticks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents play any outdoor games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so. No. Me father I don't think was never athletic. My husband was b
ut - no, and I think my mother always had too much to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - got a - two boxfulls upstairs, haven't got them out yet. Well they would - oh can't think - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 Tolstoy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  and l
ike - things like that. Tolstoy on the Hearth, I remember that because I bought him one for a Christmas box, I've still got it by the way. Oh it was very good literature chap. He was well educated was my dad. My - my - my husband always says he was one of
 the best writers he ever saw. Beautiful writer you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were there any newspapers in the house, did you have newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. We got the daily - it was the North Star we get in those days. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 
Northern}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  Star or the North Star. Now it is the Northern Echo. That's it, North Star it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were there any magazines in the house, do you remember any?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, I don't think - I can't - remember - we would get some comics, I don't know, but I can't remember, we didn't - if we did we got one, we shared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Your father was a keen reader, did your mother read as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, mother - wasn't a very good reader. Well, she was - she could read, but - she never sort of read books. The daily paper was about her - as far as she had time for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember your mother or father ever reading aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. When we were young we used to sit round and - mother used to read. She even read to my daughter when she was little
 just the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So she used to read aloud to you?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Read aloud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Children seem to enjoy that don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 They do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they ever read aloud to each other, without the children there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You mean - oh I couldn't say. No, not to - not when we were about. What they did at night, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Not in the family, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember any particular funeral at all before the end of the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Yes, I remember our next door neighbour. She had a daughter she'd had measles and - she went blind through it. Then she went to the blind school at York and
 came - when she came back, called her Topsy Robinson, she was - used knit on a knitting machine and she knitted socks and stockings for the Scotch Wool Shop, it used to be the Scotch Wool Shop. And of course people round about, customers round about, and
 
that's where we got all our - socks, and I had long stockings over me knee for the winter. They were thickish in those days, but - they definitely lasted me father our yet. Father didn't like socks, he always had stockings, he had them up to here. Yes. An
d - I remember Mr Robinson - her father, was very aristocratic looking gentleman he was. And he died, and that's the first person I ever saw dead.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 About seventy-seven I think he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would you be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh
 - about fifteen - sixteen or something like that. And I went to see him. Never seen anybody laid out before. But he had a - like a father Christmas style but not - a Van Dyck beard, he always had a nice lovely Van Dyck one. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 I was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  amazed. He looked to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  mar
vellous. And they said, touch him. And touched him. But - I never been frightened, that was my first - I never would see anybody before you know, but - I don't go to see them now but I mean, your own family but - just shows you. Always remember - I can pi
cture him now. This gentleman. White - he had a shock of hair, a shock of white hair. Moustache, A Van Dyck beard. Laid so peaceful, beautiful. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember any funerals before 1918, you were born in 1905 weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Before you were fourteen did you remember any funerals then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh I should think there would be some but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You don't remember any details?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think we - we didn't have any relations here. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you visit friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go as a family visiting friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Oh yes. I - I'm sorry. We - we - we had an uncle that was as a farm at Newton Morrell, just outside Darlington. Well he 
worked on the farm, he was a farm hand, mother's brother. And we used to go there after we finished the milk on a Sunday. We used to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It's a long way isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well, we went every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who went, the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mother and the boys and me. It was a lovely - lovely - especially when she had the plums, Victoria plums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you visit neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, mother never was a - just this - I tell you, this lady next door. But we never went and sat in one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10563601\charrsid6187387 another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you taken shopping at all, you said you used to help your mother with the shopping didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Mother - mother and I used to go shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father ever take you shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Well, he did when we were younger, he use
d to - I always remember every Saturday he used to go down - that was hen he was - all right, to Vose's, there used to be a shop called Vose's. And he used to buy us all sweets, it was a treat. Used to bring home a big packet of sweets, half a pound of th
is and - quarter or this and a quarter of that and - we dished them all out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father ever do any other shopping that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Just one he - oh - it's getting too late now. Yes. He bought us all our twenty-firsts. A watch, by the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You say your say your father used to take you to the Carl Rosa Opera company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Would I be twenty-one in 1918.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No you'd be fourteen up to the age of fourteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh. All right.
