t
 was a cinema. And incidentally, used to take me every week there and that's where the first music teacher I had was the lady that played the piano at the pictures. And I went for a year to her. And then she had - yes, they called her Mrs Nicholson, and s
he had to give over through ill health. So - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 taking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  me back into history that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go anywhere else just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember any outings with your parents at all, perhaps on Bank Holiday, before you had the milk business do you remember any?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No, we didn't. No. Must made our own -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And I suppose when you had the milk business you'd be too busy to go wouldn't you really to all go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever get away for a holiday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I'd did. Yes. I went to Wolsingham every year. Three weeks. I was lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who did you stay with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 With my - my - with my father's mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did any other members of the family go with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you do when you were at Wolsingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well I had about one, two, three - four aunties there at the time so of course I spent a lot of time round about. And - father's sister, she had an hotel called the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 Station}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  Hotel. I used to love to go down there because she had a piano and I could practice. And she used to be - annoyed because her daughter wouldn't - couldn't play as good as me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was she older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, she's younger do you see, but she's - she would never bother with the left hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days, you'd still be delivering milk wouldn't you, but before you had the milk round do you remember how you spent Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't know whether - I don't think that we - there
 was no Saturday morning pictures in those days, were there. Well I'd help mother to do the work. In those days we had - old fashioned fireplaces and see - used to scour our steps, I can remember washing the step, putting the sandstone on, yes. Used to lo
ve that. Used to do the next door neighbours too. And wash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
windows. I think that was me Saturday morning's job. Chores. Clean windows and - yes, after I got - then the back, the toilet. Called them the lavatories in those days didn't they. And - and the
 same with - used to love scouring these steps. It's a work of art you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 To try and get it even?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. When - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You used a donkey stone did they call it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 A proper sandstone from the quarry. Some were better than others, you 
bought the store - at the shops you know, local shops and - you sort of had to wash your step, then wet it, wet the sandstone, like you do like a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 pumice stone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  style, sand it along right on the edge and then you had to get your fingers and go nice and smoot
h. Oh yes. Yes, yes. I remember doing it. And then, later on, we - my mother used to always - I don't know where she got that idea from - but the stone floors, milk that had gone sour on the floor darkness it. Goes lovely. And on the top of the step where
 
the stone step was, the little bit that does in there - now everybody has them - have them red haven't they. Painted red. That's right. But - used to do that. And - the back doorsteps, just used to go over sometimes just to freshen it up. You hadn't to sa
ndstone it if there had been no bad weather you see. Just go over the top where people had stepped. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 
'Cos here was always a threshold, a threshhold and you washed the step off you had to scrub that. Anybody - woe betide anybody come in stepped on the threshband. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Funny. Don't think people bother nowadays do they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So you were busy on Saturdays helping with the chores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you had he milk business was Saturday different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How about Sundays, you were the one who went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh - at Saturday - I must tell you. Saturdays was he days that - when it was sunny weather we - had a - a - what you call - mother didn't cook a dinner on a Saturday. We always made, on a Friday night, in the summer, this is 
a lovely thing this. You slices of bread, she stewed the rhubarb when the rhubarb was first out. Slices of bread, then a layer of rhubarb over the top, another slice of bread, rhubarb. Slice of bread, rhubarb. And then - lovely quart of custard made with 
milk, over the top. Then - put it - something over the top to press it down. Oh - it's delicious cold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I think they call it summer pudding don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well it - that's it, well, we had - we used to have that. And we used to make it in a big dish.
 Delicious. So that was our Saturday dinner. Yes. Yes, it is summer pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You say you're the only one that went to church on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Except one brother went to chapel. I think they - when they was very tiny, that - we - everyone went to
 Sunday school. I'm sorry, I'm missing that. All - went when we were about three up, sorry. Well, we all went to Sunday school at three or four, then afterwards when the boys, some of the boys got older, boys are like that, they don't want to go many more
. I have children come here just the same. I'm surprised when they say they don't go to Sunday school. But you can't make them if they don't wish can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many times did you go to church on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well of course when we got the milk business I couldn't go to the morning service. But I always got to the evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have different clothes on on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. And - in those days you know, we used to wear pinafores. Have you ever seen those, old fashioned pinafores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 That covered you all over you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Oh they were lovely. And lace - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 crocheted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  lace and - the old lady next door did all this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 crocheting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
. Lovely. So mother put it on me pinafore. And I remember we could take - we used to put them on o
ur dresses to go to school as well in the summer weather. And I can remember going - wearing - dirtying it out on the Monday. 'Cos washday was Tuesday, that was before ever I took part in the washing, you see, I didn't - I used to help - I couldn't help '
til I was finished schooling could I. But - during those schooldays, yes, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You wore it Sunday and then dirtied it out on Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And dirtied it out Monday. Yes. That was your best pinafore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you play any games on Sunday? Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well we never were children that used to - think of nothing else but play, I don't know why. No. I used to like to - Sundays I used to be always poshed up and best things and - you don't think I would go and play in the street do you. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents ever attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mother went with me. Especially if I was going to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Church of England then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often did your mother go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh she used to go - and she used to go at the - of course they didn't have presentations at the Church of England. But - when there was anything special on, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She just went on special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Just because you were taking part in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Which church was it you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 St Paul's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mostly in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Me father - me father - was made to go - made - what you call actually 
made to go, mother used to take him and leave him and he always vowed that he'd never do that with any of his children and that's why we were all free lances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You could please yourself whether you went or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. And then she made him practice
 and when he was young, if he didn't - if he wouldn't practice, not like children nowadays, do you know what she did with him? I always think it was a terrible thing, it wasn't. She used to tie his - she was a very strong little woman - she used to tie hi
s thumbs, and he - she used to have a nail and he had to stand, he'd be torturous wouldn't she - yes, yes, he had his thumbs tied - 'til he gave in that he would practice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 'She would have a nail on the wall you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, on the top of the door, on the top of the door, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Rather like being on a rack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. I've heard that. I thought it was 1 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It is like torture isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. And I think that was why he rebelled when she wanted him to be this - draughtsman you see, and he w
as always very clever chap, and he went to the works one day and he says, come back he says, I've got a job, I'm going to be a moulder. She went sky high. Can imagine it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 
who was very fiery - I know when I used to go for me holidays I used to be very, very careful. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Couldn't cross her. She wasn't a bit like mother. And that's why he vowed - that he would never make any of his own - I - I couldn't believe it. That's what he said. How old he was I don't know. Whether he was about ten or eleven or what I don't 
know. But he was very clever. You know, very - very rebellious. And he did rebel afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were there any Sunday school outings that you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, we always went on a Sunday school outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did you go, can you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 We had a - we'd have a field day in the summer or we'd have a little trip to Redcar. Oh we always went on those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What other social activities organised by the church did you take part in? Did you belong to anything else at church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Ye
s, the youth - I used to go to - I used to go to Mrs Clayton's Sunday school, she was the - the vicar's wife. And they used to have socials. And we used to - that was generally on a Saturday evening, take your boyfriend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you say the vicar's wife had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Mrs Clayton. She used to have the over fourteens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 From the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
We were the young ladies class then, we used to go to the vicarage of a Sunday afternoon. Never used to miss that. Always went to that. Used to like to go t
o that. And then we had social evening on a Saturday evenings and if not at our own we used to go to Lowson Street, another neighbouring - a chapel. Or St Marks. See, you go like they do now, nowadays, from different youth clubs they go from one youth clu
bs to another don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And it doesn't matter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  denomination it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Well it didn't then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I never realized the chapel and church worked in together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But the Catholics didn't. Funny. Catholics never invited you. They don't now do they? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you belonged to the choir, how old would you be when you went in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would I be - I'd be about twelve or thirteen, twelve I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember any activities that the choir had, did you take part in any activities? Did you go on any outings with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. No, we just went on - when they had this summer outing. The choir outing used to call it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did you go for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh different places. Maybes in the country sometimes I don't k
now. Sort of Reeth. Go the dales. I don't know whether we went to Redcar. I know we did later on but that - that was much later in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How many times did you have to sing in the choir on Sunday, just the Sunday evening was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I never - I didn't sing solos, I was just in the choir. Yes. Yes. Evensong, six o'clock it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so. I never took part in it if they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When we were children they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who would say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Me father I think. Father would say grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 All used to say them silently.
 Always been taught when we were quite young. Is it going off? Must have been taught when we were very young because I know we used to say them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever have family prayers, all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. He was what you call a Socialist. An I.L.P. isn't it. Socialist I.L.P. Yes. Yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Why do you think he held those views?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh well, he used to say it was better for the working man, that's all I'm thinking of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. She just used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you know what her views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She just voted the same as dad. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 
Yes, because - her sister - her sister she had, her husband voted Labour, he was the same with - but you see, mother's - with being on the land, farmers, they were all Tories in those days, Tory. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And auntie would never - never change her views. Mother used to say well the vote was no good to our family if one voted Labour and one voted the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So she voted the same as your father then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Just because of that, no other reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Just because she wanted to be the same as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well she would vote - if she were to vote she would vote, for the local elections as well as the Parliamentary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted different
ly from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Yes, he did. No, I mean - he used to get in arguments - but he still would stick to his course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But he didn't feel that he had to vote for a particular party because of the people who employed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
His views were Socialism. Socialistic views - definitely. And he ad a - a great friend that used to - one of his friends was Pearson Harrison, I don't know whether you've heard of this Pearson Ha
rrison. He got to be one of our oldest councilors, Alderman Harrison, who died just a little while back. And he - he was a - the Socialist. And there was a - I think, the first M.P. that came here, can remember they were friends. My father went to see him
, can't remember his name. But - Ramsey McDonald was a favourite of me father's. And Atlee was a favourite of me father's. I can't remember anything else. Sorry. That was later years though I'm talking about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In some places at that time men felt }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It was just his own idea was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You say he was a member of the Socialist party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother ever work for any of the parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was she a member of the Socialist party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time? You said your mother was a needlewoman and your father played the violin, any other ways in which they spent their time when they weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Oh me father had a garden, two gardens. So me - plenty to do there when he wasn't - and - and me mother - well there was always mending, darning, make do. I've never seen anybody like her. She was happy. Happy doing it. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She - she used to go with me occasionally afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where would you go, up to you being the age of fourteen or fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
We - we - well - just depends you see, if father took me - somebody had to stay in with the children. The other children weren't there. So - when we ever went there was always one at home. So - yes, so if - if I - sometimes something
 special she probably would go to the theatre with me. Later on, that much later, she went with us every week hen we got older, you know what I mean, but you're talking about the early days aren't you. Yes. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go out with your mother on your own then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Yes. We used to go just occasionally. She - she didn't like pictures, mother. Didn't like pictures at all - cinemas. But she liked the - live theatre, she called it the live theatre, if it was a good show. But she really - wasn't musical
 in the sense that me father and I were, you know what I mean. Enjoyed shows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So if you went out to a show it was usually with your father then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Before your father stopped work as a moulder do you remember what time he got home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't - five o'clock or half past five wasn't it. Five o'clockish I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 those}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  days how many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well he didn't go out very often. 'Cos if you got out he used to get too wo
rse for drink so he didn't bother to go. No. So he'd bring a bottle of beer in with him. That was why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often did he play the violin at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 parties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - sometimes just - sometimes must once a week. Sometimes not - nothing - just depen
ds. Twenty-firsts, they were all friends that used to say - and - would he go and play for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 their}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 twenty-first and this pianist. I didn't used to play at the parties mind you, this Mr Dent used to play and he used to get all these little engagements for him
. And the Speedwell, I can remember he got him to go to the Speedwell Hotel, you know, it's still there now in Victoria Road, you know it. Before it was modernized. And - he used to play and there was a weekly dance there on a Friday night. Well that's on
e of them that I used to go to turn the music over. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you had the milk business, how many evenings a week would your father spend at home, just the same number would it be or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, or - or at the garden, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs? Well he played at them didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, he didn't play at clubs. No. When he - before he was married, but not after. Don't know whether he was a member of Northgate Club, I don't think he was. I don't think he was ever a 
member of a club, my dad. Used to - just buy what he wanted - from an off free }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So he didn't go to pubs regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother ever go to pubs or clubs with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Mother never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father take part in any sport, you told me no didn't you, he wasn't a sportsman, an outdoor man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he attend the races at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 About - twice a year I should imagine. Once on the Derby, a shilling now and then, so you woul
dn't call that nothing would he. Mother was the same, we just used to bet for the jockey, Donaghue. That's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, any boot club, sick club, funeral club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 He - yes, he belonged - the Order - he was in the Order of the Druids.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Is that a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well, yes, it is a sick club. And he was - me mother was in - what they call a - at those days, finished now, Rise Carr Benefit Club and he used to go - was it on
ce a fortnight to pay a shilling at the end of the year, Christmas time, used to draw out and get something, you know, it was - about a guinea or twenty-one shillings or something like that. But the - what happened was, if any person had died the - the me
mbers got paid, there were the members and members wives paid you see so they called it Rise Carr Benefit Club, if you've ever heard of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So really it was a like a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 Christmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  savings club wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But if anybody died you got the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
The people would get the money, that's why you wouldn't get all that you paid in, you see, but - it's been finished a few years now. But still it was a good thing in those days if you got about twenty-one shillings for Christmas wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How did you get on with your brothers, you said were one big family didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - oh not bad. I was always called - I think - I was always wanting to be the boss I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Through being the only girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Can - I can imagine that. I don't know whether I always got me own way, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was there one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well in later years I daresay I would then. My youngest brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But before leaving school were you close to any particular brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think I was. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh well, I had - two friends used to go to - used to go out with, went to school with me. Incidentally they're both dead now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they live near to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So they were neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Just across the - yes - just across the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you play out with your brothers at all, you played indoor games with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, indoors, no. Not when we - they had their own pals, just the same as they have nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did you play with these two girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well - my father had a swing put up in our yard, we used to play on that and then we used to play in those days on the pavements. If you wanted to play outdoors - with a - chalk the pavement, one, tw
o, three, four, so and so on. Hopscotch. Play hopscotch - yes. Our boys used to play - marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Outside on the pavement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. In the gutter, you know, glass ollies and what not. And - I think Easter we always played whip and top and - oh that wa
s it, thing I got - shuttlecock and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 battledore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
. That was about all, and you used to play them in the street in those days. Because - there weren't the motor cars, just horses and carts come down. You could get out the road of those couldn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever have the children in your home to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Had this - one of my friend's - young daughters, when she was - she was much younger than her. About six or seven years younger so she had to find her you see. And she used to come over and come in to h
ave a swing. That's about the only child I know that we ever had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever go into their homes to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. But I liked coming to me own home best. Because I never like her mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What didn't you like about her mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well - this Friday night - I tell you, bath night. Every Friday night, I can always remember that, they all had to be - take }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 Beecham's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 Pills. Every Friday night and there was - one, two, three, four - there was one boy in the room, there was five girls - no, four g
irls and one boy, we were the opposite, four boys and one girl you see. So this night, she says, come along, she said - here - I think thou'll have to have it chance. Very broad she was this person. So - and - I can't - I - I can't swallow. So she - we al
l had this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 Beecham's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 Pills on a spoonful of jam. So she puts it in front of me. Eat all the jam off, I still had the pill. So she give me another spoonful. I'll never forget it as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 long}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  as I live. In this spoonful of jam and - oh I could - I could never get it down }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And you never liker her because of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No, that's why I didn't like her. And - I - from - incidentally, from now I can eat - take any kind of pills but I - I would never swallow them. Used to put them in me mouth and push 'em d
own, and gulp and they're down. And another thing I didn't like her for. She used to go buy eggs from us, when we sold the eggs you see, and she used to say, I don't want any duck now, I didn't want any cock eggs. Oh I thought that was dreadful. I used to
 say, what does she mean? Well, little tiny ones. So of course I never went to play, but I liked the daughter, but I didn't like - so you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well I suppose so but I never did. I'm like my daughter. Everybody says my daughter never got dirty, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well I don't think there was any - very bad children round our way at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You don't remember ever being told not to play with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No. No. Well - I think I was very choosy, I wouldn't play with anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What made you choosy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh I've always been choosy. Very particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who wouldn't you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well I wouldn't play with - what I call - scruffy little kids for a start, if they looked dirty or anything like that. But I wouldn't pick on them. Just not - play with them that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you belong to any youth organisations besides the church club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No. There weren't any organisations then, there weren't like club night like - such as ours, the only thing I joined was the Co-operative choir. Young choir.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - I'd b
ee about fourteen when I first joined. I was in about two - two years or something like that. But I got too old you see. The Junior choir it was called. The Co-operative Junior Choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often did you sing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - we did loads of concerts. Yes. All over - all over Darlington, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school, you obviously played the piano, did you have any other hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I liked to draw. And I - I liked needlework. I've always liked needlework. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you keep any pets at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No, just used to go and watch. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 
Pick the peas when they were ready, used to love to go when the peas were ready.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Our boys used to - our boys used to go fishing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. 'Cos I can remember them getting worms for the bait.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You said sometimes you walked to Newton Morrell didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. On Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go for other walks at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. We walked - we walked all over - Darlington. I've always been a good walker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you walk out into the country when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Me father used to take me brothers but I didn't - never went on those. Up to this - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  this way where my husband goes nowadays. Right round the golf course this way. Round the top end of the town you know, round Skirningham way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But you didn't go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, never had a bicycle. I - I tried once and I fell off. I never bothered any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you went for walks who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh well with friends, with your friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 With your girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No. Just - at - when we were at the school we'd take part in the school sports but I never - never a very good runner. Just middling you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you go to any theatres, concerts, music halls and cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes, Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Couldn't say, I imagine so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Any idea how much you had, can you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - think about a shilling each that's all we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you think you'd have it regularly every week or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well me father used to buy these sweets, I tell you, that was part of our pocket money. But we'd - if we wanted to go anywhere special we just used to ask. And if it wasn't too dear -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You'd get extra money then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you had your pocket money what did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well sweets and - or saving up to - to buy presents for one another's birthdays. We had a little - we all had a little piggy bank, yes. And - sometime me brothers used to get the knife 
out to have a go, to see if they could get a copper out for some sweets, you know, stick the knife up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Raid the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 had a - a kind neighbour used to, next door, the next door neighbour. If she ever - if she was ill or anything like that, but nothing - I can't remember mother being ill from - from that - our - after I were helping. No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You don't remember her ever being ill after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, just colds and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember what happened when your younger brothers were born? Who helped then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 There was a lady came in. Incidentally her son is married to my friend now. And she came and waited on - Mrs Walker they
 called her, our Treasurer, her mother-in-law and she - yes, and she - used to - come - I think - on - two - there was only two born in that street - in that street where we had the milk business, in Shildon Street. The one next to me was born after we ca
m
e to Darlington in Gurnery Street. And - hen - I can't remember anything about him. I - I think she same then. I'm not sure. No - auntie came then to look after mother, mother's - mother's oldest sister. Then I think in Shildon Street this Rosanna they ca
lled her, she came. She wasn't married then. She came. And then she came for both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And you paid her to come in did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I expect they would do, yes, me father was working then. But - I wouldn't be very old you see at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did 
your parents have any relatives living nearby, there was one at Newton Morrell who you saw every Sunday, any other relative nearby, would you call Wolsingham nearby or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. About thirty - thirty miles away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Any other relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often would you see the people at Wolsingham, you said you went on holidays every year, would you see them at other times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Sometimes - did they used to come down for Easter Monday - occasionally. They did later on in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 life}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  but they didn't - sometimes - mother would maybes have a day up there. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But you didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 visit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  them regularly at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents have friends, you said sometimes your father used to invite people in for a musical evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Father's friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were they your father's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Well, they were mother's as well I expect but - they were men that worked with my father I mean. And the wives. Their wives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where did they see them, just in your home or did they go to their houses as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I think I think I can remember going round once to their house, one of them, one of his special friends. It wasn't many. Just - two of them, we didn't go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 pianist\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  house but he used to come to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother and father share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Mother was always - docile - person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother have friends of her own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. We made lots of friends with having the milk business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father have friends of his own or only those, he shared with your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I don't know, he never brought any home, I couldn't say. But he didn't have a - a friend like as you say now, a certain person to go out every night with. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 These friends who came in and enjoyed his music, they were people that he worked with when he worked as a moulder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How often did they come into the house to make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - that was about once a month or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember if they were offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Because they used to bring the bottles in. Just have a - bottle of beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 prefer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  to bring it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, and he used to bring - and the ladies would have - tea, mother would make sandwiches and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was this on any particular day or occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Sunday nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your fathers friends or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Friends of both they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did friends call in casually without an invitation ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't know, I should imagine so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did neighbours ever call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, if she wanted anything, you know, to see mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did any other neighbours pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, another one at the back used to - back of our house, about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think you
r parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours, they made music didn't they, they do anything else when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. Just talk probably. One of the - I must tell you this bit - one of the - the cha
p that - the chappie that made my dad his violin, this special one that, he came from Lancashire. Yorkshire Moors. We used to love to go - and we used - oh we passed - sorry - we used to go around to his house. Two or three with mother and father and that
, and he used to read these odd poems in the Yorkshire dialect. Yes. And - we used to love to go there. And he lived in Henry Street. About - next street. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 
And he was lame - his wife was lame I should have said, not him, but he made this violin that my dad had that we passed on to my daughter. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Incidentally a chap came the other week, he would have liked to have bought it. I won't part with it for sentimental reasons. But it's very heavy, but if you ever want to part with it, but my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 
daughter,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  when she first grew up you know, in the high school, she was in the school orchestra. She had this. She's never played it since she left school. That's incidentally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You used to go to his house then and he used to read his poems?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 And do you know, I\rquote ve 
I have a whole a roll of them, I can picture them somewhere, they must be down at the old house somewhere. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
I'm always going to have a look, I hope me brother hasn't done away with them 'cos I think now I'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 relish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 them. Like to learn some of them. And he us
ed to write poems too, in the Yorkshire dialect. In them days you see, the people made their own amusements. And we used to love, we used to say - are you going down to Mr Howard's tonight dad? Yes. And our boys would like to go then. But he used to say -
 it was so funny, listening to somebody in a proper Yorkshire dialect, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So you went as a family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Remember that. That's just come back to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When your parents got together with their friends - did they play games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No, we just - the only games that were played were in our own house, in our own family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Well - some we used to call a bit - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 rather}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  snobbish didn't you. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Can you tell me what the different classes were, you had the snobbish people, what other classes were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well you'd call them - do you call them middle c
lass? And - I - I had some customers that used to be like that. Liked to think they were better off than what you were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You'd come into contact with all sorts in the milk business wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You do nowadays don't you. But - we got on very well with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 everyone}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  really. Well I always have done, can talk to anyone me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well, I wouldn't call myself middle class. Call myself working class. Yes. I - I - I don't want to be snobbish, I wouldn'
t like to feel snobbish but I wouldn't like to go down. I like to keep my head good. I'd rather be - what do you call it - I suppose it is more like middle class, you'd like to be - but it's no good going above your station, that's how I always find. Don'
t you? Well you wouldn't like to appear and talk big. To be something you're not, that's what I meant, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well all the people that we lived in our district were definitely working clas
s people. We were in a working class area. I don't know about you, but you see, yours is in a middle class area where you're living now. That makes a difference. The west end of the town was always - called - middle class area. Definitely. Yes. Now when y
ou lived up our area of the town, it was called the working class. Did you not know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of people belonged to the other classes you mentioned, who belonged to the snobbish class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well no people around our district. Would ever be middl
e class - belong to the middle class section. I tell you, you'd have to go further - to a different district. A new town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of jobs would they have, these people in the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well the majority of them would be clerks and - what you call - what is it, collar and tie jobs isn't it, you call that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 That's right, white collar workers. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And who would the snobbish people be, what sort of jobs did they have?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well you see, once you got to that and you were a collar and tie person, the - the idea was that they thought they were better than you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Just because of the jobs they did you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. But nowadays - you can't tell one from the other because there's as many working class people have cars - ther
e's more people - working class people have cars nowadays than - yes. But - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  the - what it was in those days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Can you remember}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387  being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you ever taught to curtsey or shoe respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
No. I never had - the only Royalty I've ever had any contact with - well, not Royalty - ladies, is our Lady Stamerer, and I'm afraid I've never curtsied to her yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 She's a charming person isn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Very well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was there anyone that you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In Darlington who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
People such as - you mean tradesmen? Well I would say councilors were considered important, if you got to be a councilor you got important. And - I should imagine - most tradesmen in those days were considered important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you come into contact with them, you'd come into contact with the trades people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. You did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you come into contact with the councilors at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, just if we - we delivered to their houses or something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Why do you think the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 tradesmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well - for the simple reason they were supposed to have more money I think than the working class. That was why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who did the shopkeepers associate with, who did they have for friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well we didn't have any shopkeepers as friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who do you think the shopkeepers would have as friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I should imagine they would have other shopkeepers wouldn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who do you think the clergy would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well they should - they should associate with all the people in their parish shouldn't they. They don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you notice if they had any particular friends when you were a schoolchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The Reverend Curtain was our vicar at St Paul's, in our parish, because we were north of it you see. He w
as very nice I think. He wasn't nice as what the - the first - the old chap that used to be there before was called Canon Hutchinson and everyone said he was a real gentleman. Now he'd speak to anyone. Now I have a chappie - chappie over here, the ministe
r from the Manse. Minister isn't it - do you know, he passes - and I go to his chapel - he passes you by in the street. I always thought that ministers should speak to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 everyone}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  they see. Now the Reverend Tidwell you see, called in today, I don't go to his church. Different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In those days then did you think the clergy associated with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. They }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 reckoned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  - they used to say that Mr Clayton as very - a bit stand offish, but Mrs Clayton was a very charming woman, she had - three daughters. We 
used - I tell you, I used to love to go to her Sunday school. 'Cos she used to make us a cup of tea as well, I think - whether that - that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Who did - he teachers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 The teachers? I don't know. Because I don't think any - any of the
 teachers that we had - that I knew - belonged our end of the town at all. So I couldn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And farmers, who do you think they had as friends, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well farmers naturally. They keep to their own, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And who did the employers associate with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Employees? Oh - oh well they're the same. They kept to their own. Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well people, I would say, that - that had faith. That's all I can say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And who do you think went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well the same people. And there were mostly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  used to go. Loads of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 trade\rquote s people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 used to go to church and chapel? Yes, 'cos it used to be the - the well known things years ago that - oh yes, have to go to church to keep appearances up and especially of the customers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you think there was any difference between church and chapel people at all, you said you got together for some social activities?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I don't think there was. I was 
brought up as Church of England you see and - I always went. I changed. And my daughter, she didn't like church. She was christened - christened at church but she went with a friend, and incidentally her friend was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 Alderman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  Turner's daughter. He died recen
tly. And she made friends with her at school so she joined the chapel, Lowson Street - chapel. And eventually I joined their choir. But I don't go anywhere now, I've stopped. I - I'm a free lance, I go anywhere I wish. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where you lived did all the
 working class people have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups even within the working class group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 There were different groups. Some were much poorer. In fact, I think, we after we had the business and we worked 
hard afterwards, when we got on our feet as you might say, I think we were what you call better off. But - it never went - that far that we forgot the people we were living with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Could you describe a family within each group, you say there were the po
orer people in the working class, could you just describe one of those families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well there was a - a family that lived down our street. They had a lot of children. And he was very poor was the father I think. And mother was ill. I remember we - we -
 mother made up a great parcel of things that were too small for our children and they had - they were smaller you see, we grew up a bit then. Only socks and vests that we'd grown out of. Clean, you know, and they weren't old but they just were - the - we
ll they was too small for our boys. And I can remember taking them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 down}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 to this house. And she - she said - when I want charity, she said, I'll ask for it. It upset mother. She never bothered any more after that. Never forgot that lady. You see, I mean to s
ay, you see, so when you said about - not like nowadays well in those days there weren't jumble sales. There weren't any Definitely not. You just passed on if you - well I had some things passed on to me that were good. But that's - oh it hurt mother, ver
y much. And I took them. And I had to bring them back. And they had - about eight children and they were all smaller than us. Wouldn't you have thought......
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were the children well cared for normally or not in this poorer sort of working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well - some of them looked - one of the little girls - I can see a little girl just now - as if they were frozen to death you see. She thought she was doing a good turn. Well I suppose there's some people like that nowadays isn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In the working classes do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I - I should imagine so. I don't know of any special case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh well I think that's the - that's the way right through up to today, don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 You think that's nothing to do with classes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes, I think - there would be that little distinction - i
f a - if a chap - chap was working and he had a trade - he were supposed to be better off than a man that was just an ordinary labourer, now this man that I was speaking was just an ordinary labourer so he wouldn't have much money. They wouldn't get - the
y didn't get much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 as a tradesman if they come down - they got a few shillings more than what a labourer did you see. And if you say, oh he's only a labourer. Oh yes, he's a tradesman. So there must have been - there must have been, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did your mother and father and have the same attitude to people in different classes, did they treat everybody alike or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009605\charrsid6187387 Oh I couldn't - I think - I think me mother was very, very easy going, me father wasn't. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And - he wouldn't let - sometimes mother got put on - 'cos she was so easy going, you know, she'd let people ride over the top of her but me father wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did they normally treat people the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Whether they were poor, rich or whatever class they were in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No - I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was it possible at that time to move }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  one class to another, can you remember anyone who did? Well you say you moved up the working class really didn't you as you got the milk business going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember anyone else who sort of moved up within the working classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, I don't think so. No, not any particular person, family or anything. No. It's a rather difficult question that isn't it. Yes. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. The old man that died next door to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 He was a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
She - her husband - his wife used to play war. She was - she talked and talked and talked and talked, she could talk for evermore. But he was always very aristocratic and he always had a stick, a silver mounted top, and a trilby hat i
n those days. You know, I can picture him now. And they used to say, oh yes - he thinks himself a gentleman. He always did - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was there anyone you can think of as described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I was frightened of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Why was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 He lived in the next street and at that time, when I was a girl, there was a new school being built. And - that was one thing 
we did, must tell you that, forgot about that. And one night we went with some friends and we were walking on the wall - it was lightish nights too. You know, like you walk on a wall. And the bobby came round, they shout, here's the bobby. Of course, he c
a
ught me. I told you I couldn't run didn't I? So he said, what's your name? I said, what they call me, Lilah Currace. Where do you live? 50 Shildon Street. Right. Run all the way home. Panting all the time. All at one a knock come to the door. And I said, 
the bobby's coming to our house. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 
And - he come in and he said, I just want to tell you, Mrs Currance, he said, that you're daughter - will you keep your child off the - off the building, he says, I've been told to keep them, he says, they will go on these -
 walking round, and it was just in the process. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
And he says, I think I frightened her to death. She said, you did. He says, I - I'm very sorry, he says, I frightened her that much, but I thought if I do come and say - oh never forgot P.C.O'Neill. No, and t
hat's all it was, he just used to warn. Didn't do anything. Just - we just were - we shouldn't have been there - shouldn't have been there. That's one instance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Where you were naughty did your mother ever say I'll call a policeman or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
How do you think the treated the people in general, he sounds as though he was quite considerate really, how did he treat the rest of the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 I think he was very good, really - yes. But he was always on the beat, he was always there, that's wh
at we were saying about. He was on the beat now - they used to say, if the kid - boys were playing in the street and that - oh, get off the road, her's bobby coming. Bobby O'Neill. It was bobby O'Neill. He was really; very jovial. Stout - very stout. Do y
ou know incidentally he's just died last year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Your home was rented, did you see anything of the landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, it belonged to a concern. Thomas Clayhills and son it was called - that owned a brewery and they had a lot of houses. And - I th
ink the reason we got that house was - I don't know whether it was better than the one over in Gurney Street or what it was, but we were in a long time in that one in Shildon Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 So you wouldn't see anything of your landlord then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 We had an agent. No, just had an agent come. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you feel about him as acting on behalf of the landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh he was very nice, was a nice chap, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet, I think you sa
id that the only time was when your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 We did when me father was ill. And - you see he was off quite a while before we took the milk business and I mean there wasn't any }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 dole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  in those days. So me mother felt the pinch then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you think about that, do you remember anything particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No, well you wouldn't have the money would you. Coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or our of work, well you say you had no dole coming in or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. There wasn't any dole in those days. He just had his sick pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was this illness before you had the milk business the only one you remember your father having?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Yes. He never worked any more. Not in the foundry he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did you say his illness was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
It was - in the moulding, the - what is - what's it to do with - fumes and that isn't it. Well - some - sometimes men - miners get it in the cola pit don't they. Well - whatever it was - processed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music, like banging on pans and what have you, shouts of get out?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No No evictions or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Whose ideas was it that you took the milk business, was that your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 It was me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How did that come about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
Well - when we - I wanted a little bit of pocket money of me own, like some of the girls, with me dad being out of work I went to work at this place and it's awful near, this friend that I have now, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  was her husband's grandmother that had this milk business. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 So}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 
 I went to deliver milk in the summer holidays. Home from school. And anyhow, eventually she wanted to sell the business. So I - I said, why don't you get it mother. Oh yes, get it. And - of course I said I liked - I loved going roun
d. I loved to going to other - I always have liked going to people. And that's how it started. No, it was a bright idea. Our boys used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 curse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387  it years later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes it seems to have got hour family on its feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Were you ever given lessons by your parents at all before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh yes. Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What did he teach you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh - as soon as I were - name and address. He taught us to - read - to count. Nursery rhymes. Oh - long before we went to school. 'Cos - 
I've just remembered now. When I was three I got lost. We lived in Gurney Street then and moved to - one Monday and I was picked up on Blackwell - at Grange Road - down the Grange Road. I don't know how I come to be there but that's where I was. And this 
m
an was coming into town and he brought in - brought me in and took to the old police station in Northgate. And I told them me name and address and a policeman - mother was frantic all over the town looking for me. And - never thought about looking at the 
p
olice station. And - the policeman came and said, if you have a mind to come your little daughter's sitting at the police station. When I got, it shows you, I was sitting having a cup of tea with a policeman and a biscuit. Just - just remind me, so me fat
her must have been well - I must have been well taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 But he didn't give you any definite lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 When you first started what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 And when did you come back?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Was it twelve o'clock - half past twelve was it. No, twelve o'clock, then go back half past one - 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 How old were you when you started afternoon school, when you started going all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Oh, I went all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Right from the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Yes. Right up to the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Then you - went half time didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 In the war, yes, and we had to come to a school here because the soldiers were in our schools. And that was when I was perf
ect. At that time at our old school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 What kind of a school was it that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14690632 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11696315\charrsid6187387 Well - they call them now secondary modern don't they. We started at a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403854\charrsid6187387 
